findings.lower_chest: Mild dependent atelectasis, normal lung fields, no pleural or pericardial effusion.

abdominal.hepatobiliary: Liver normal, mild periportal edema, no focal lesions, normal gallbladder.
abdominal.pancreas: Normal attenuation, no focal lesions or ductal dilatation.
abdominal.urinary: Normal kidneys with no focal lesions or hydronephrosis.

gastrointestinal.small_bowel: Normal caliber and wall thickness, enhancement.
gastrointestinal.appendix: Dilated at 1.1 cm, thickened wall with adjacent fat stranding, no perforation or abscess.
gastrointestinal.colon: Mild thickening of cecal wall, remaining colon within normal limits.

abdominal.pelvis: Unremarkable urinary bladder and distal ureters.

reproductive_organs.uterus: Enlarged with a large, submucosal fibroid (5.8 x 4.8 cm), moderate fluid in endometrium.
reproductive_organs.adnexa: Cystic structure in right adnexa (1.6 x 1.8 cm) likely representing a corpus luteum cyst, trace pelvic fluid.

abdominal.vascular: No abdominal aortic aneurysm or atherosclerotic disease.
abdominal.bones: No acute fractures or worrisome osseous lesions, bilateral pars defects at L5-S1 with mild anterolisthesis.
